# Atome Card Support — Project Overview

A customer service bot management system with two roles: Manager and Customer.
Single monorepo with client/ (frontend) and server/ (backend).

- Manager configures the bot at route /manager (password: atome2024)
- Customer interacts with the bot at route /

## Tech Stack

| Layer          | Choice                                             |
| -------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| Frontend       | React 19 + TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS v4       |
| Backend        | Python 3.11 + FastAPI, async/await, Pydantic       |
| LLM            | Gemini API (google-generativeai SDK, direct calls) |
| Persistence    | JSON files only (config.json, mistakes.json)       |
| Deployment     | Docker + docker-compose                            |
| Component libs | shadcn/ui, HeroUI                                  |

## Hard Rules — Never Violate These

- Never use LangChain or LangGraph
- Never use a database. JSON files only
- Never use localStorage for critical state
- All LLM calls go through FastAPI backend, never directly from frontend
- All API keys live in server/.env only, never in frontend
- Frontend and backend are decoupled via REST API only
- No SSR. Pure CSR only

## Repo Structure

- client/ → Vite + React frontend
- server/ → FastAPI backend
- docker-compose.yml → at monorepo root
- .env → at monorepo root, copied into containers at build time
